      "cookedHtml": "<p>I would like to create an Automation that sends a daily report or information from my Task board when there are items are overdue (based on the Due Date column) and send these to the Person (based on the Person column)</p>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/5/8/58b35d86361402e98871424a38d60b49bd938b66.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/5/8/58b35d86361402e98871424a38d60b49bd938b66_2_690x178.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"178\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1445×374 77.8 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>Does anyone know if this is possible and how ? Many thanks, Antony</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 189407,
      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2024-06-18T16:40:56.735Z",
      "author": "kaylak (Kayla K)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/antonygarnett\">@antonygarnett</a> ,</p>\n<p>If you are looking for one notification that details all items that are overdue, I don’t have a solution. But if you would be okay with receiving a notification for each item that is overdue, the automation screenshotted below should work for your use case.<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/0/4/040ab6bf6cfbc586f57fe89281910a7713364cc7.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/0/4/040ab6bf6cfbc586f57fe89281910a7713364cc7.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"313\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">725×329 12.1 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 225860,
      "postNumber": 3,
      "createdAt": "2025-04-02T16:40:48.622Z",
      "author": "Iryna_Belaya (Iryna Belaya)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hello <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/antonygarnett\">@antonygarnett</a> ,<br />\nYou can achieve this easily with the <strong><a href=\"https://monday.com/marketplace/listing/10000761/board-email-reports\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Board Email Reports</a></strong> app! Here’s how it works.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You set up the following automation rule:<br />\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/b/6/b6aa91ba21bd8705054fb005566ab91075bf2efb.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/b/6/b6aa91ba21bd8705054fb005566ab91075bf2efb_2_690x292.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"292\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1462×619 95.2 KB</span></div></a></div><br />\nThe email will include a <strong>detailed Excel attachment</strong> with all the relevant data, so you don’t have to open <a href=\"http://monday.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday.com</a>:<br />\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/c/4/c490666219f696739815a0b7a14eeab91472ec36.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/c/4/c490666219f696739815a0b7a14eeab91472ec36.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"377\" height=\"483\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">377×483 20.4 KB</span></div></a></div><br />\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/e/7/e7eaeb18529f90b755eab2773fcdc55b8ca6798d.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/e/7/e7eaeb18529f90b755eab2773fcdc55b8ca6798d_2_690x176.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"176\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1285×329 47.5 KB</span></div></a></div></li>\n</ol>\n<p>You can install the app and test whether it works for you.</p>"
